<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-19169] Don&apos;t NPE when initializing CFSs for local system keyspaces with UCS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19169</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When UnifiedCompactionStrategy is used as the default, NPEs are thrown when&lt;br/&gt;
flushing the system keyspace tables early during startup. The system keyspace is&lt;br/&gt;
initialised before the cluster metadata, but UCS currently tries to access the&lt;br/&gt;
current epoch when initialising the shard manager, to determine whether the&lt;br/&gt;
local ranges are out of date. This isn&apos;t necessary for the system keyspaces as&lt;br/&gt;
they use LocalStrategy and cover the whole token space.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
