                            <comment id="17793401" author="beobal" created="Tue, 5 Dec 2023 19:06:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mostly this seems harmless, as the CFS and compaction strategy are able to be initialised as soon as the CMS is available, but we can see evidence of it occurring in tests when running the &lt;tt&gt;test-trie&lt;/tt&gt; suites.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17793402" author="beobal" created="Tue, 5 Dec 2023 19:07:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/beobal/cassandra/commits/samt/19169&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/beobal/cassandra/commits/samt/19169&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Edit: added commit to a branch batching together a few small fixes&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17793815" author="beobal" created="Wed, 6 Dec 2023 16:08:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Trivial patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/beobal/cassandra/commit/cd456f7e30f6128e67631503f0e71f44444b99cc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Circle CI runs for branch with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19169&quot; title=&quot;Don&amp;#39;t NPE when initializing CFSs for local system keyspaces with UCS&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19169&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19169&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19102&quot; title=&quot;Test Failure: org.apache.cassandra.distributed.test.ReadRepairTest#readRepairRTRangeMovementTest&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19102&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19102&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &amp;amp; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19171&quot; title=&quot;Test Failure: org.apache.cassandra.locator.PropertyFileSnitchTest.configContainsRemoteConfig-cdc_jdk17_x86_64&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19171&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19171&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: &#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/michaelsembwever/cassandra/274/workflows/6843aabd-4749-4cbf-94a5-ec3a546704e6&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;J11&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/michaelsembwever/cassandra/274/workflows/440e2e39-038e-45ba-ab91-80335a497f21&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;J17&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Aside from some strangeness with cqlshlib tests which appears completely unrelated, only failures are the ones tracked in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19072&quot; title=&quot;Test failure: org.apache.cassandra.distributed.test.log.FetchLogFromPeersTest.catchupCoordinatorAheadPlacementsReadTest-_jdk11&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19072&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19072&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19058&quot; title=&quot;Test Failure: org.apache.cassandra.simulator.test.ShortPaxosSimulationTest.simulationTest-_jdk11&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19058&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19058&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &amp;amp; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18360&quot; title=&quot;Test Failure: o.a.c.cql3.validation.operations.AlterTest#testDropListAndAddListWithSameName&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-18360&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-18360&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17794306" author="ifesdjeen" created="Thu, 7 Dec 2023 15:35:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can also use &lt;tt&gt;keyspace.getMetadata().params.replication.isLocal()&lt;/tt&gt;, but I do not know which one would be better in this context.&lt;br/&gt;
+1 otherwise!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17794354" author="beobal" created="Thu, 7 Dec 2023 17:09:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yep, definitely and &lt;tt&gt;cfs.localRangesWeighted()&lt;/tt&gt; includes a similar check which results in them using &lt;tt&gt;RING_VERSION_IRRELEVANT&lt;/tt&gt;. In the end I went with this as it seemed more to be more explicitly showing that the &lt;tt&gt;shardManager&lt;/tt&gt; can&apos;t be out of date because the version is irrelevant.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
